  "title": "Squaring function.",
  "body": " Squaring function  The two input\/output statements from nicely illustrate the asymmetry in the roles of independent variable and dependent variable mentioned in . Whereas, by definition, corresponding to each input of a function there is a unique output , it is not necessarily the case that for each output of the function there is a unique input that gets mapped to it. In this case, we see that the output is the value of at two different inputs: and . More on this later, when we discuss invertible functions.  "
