  "number": "1.1.38",
  "title": "Vertical line test.",
  "body": " Vertical line test  It might be helpful to envision the vertical line test as a scanning procedure. Imagine scanning your set with a device that produces a vertical green line that we move from left to right across the entire expanse of .   If at some moment while we are scanning from left to right our green vertical line hits two or more different points on the graph, then our scanner emits a loud error beep, indicating that has failed an -test, and declares that is not the graph of a function.    If, on the other hand, we are able to scan the entire expanse of from left to right without hearing the error beep, then has passed the -test for all vertical lines , and the scanner declares that is the graph of a function.     "
